title: Luigi Mangione arrest: Ghost gun, mask, anti-corporate writings found on suspect in CEO’s killing, says Police
description: Luigi Nicholas Mangione, 26, was arrested in Altoona, Pennsylvania, for the murder of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson. Police found a ghost gun, mask, and writings expressing anti-corporate sentiment. Mangione, a University of Pennsylvania graduate, was identified via surveillance footage and a tip. The killing has heightened corporate security concerns.
